figure_1: Latent profile analysis of skill difference in teletherapy versus in‐person therapy. FIS difference was calculated by subtracting therapists' tele‐FIS from their in‐person FIS. Positive scores indicate higher levels of skills in in‐person therapeutic scenarios, whereas negative scores indicate higher levels of skills in teletherapy scenarios. ABC, alliance bond capacity; ARRR, alliance rupture repair responsiveness; EE, emotional expression; Emp, empathy; Hope, hope/positive expectations; Per, persuasiveness; VF, verbal fluency; WAU, warmth/acceptance/understanding.
